## 5. Loading State — Skeleton Grid

**Problem:** `CircularProgress` centered on a blank page feels cold and shows no structure.

**Replace the loading early-return with a skeleton grid:**

```tsx
// Remove or replace this pattern:
// if (loading) return <Box sx={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "center", mt: 8 }}><CircularProgress /></Box>

// Instead, show skeleton cards in the same grid layout:
if (loading) {
  return (
    <Container maxWidth="xl" sx={{ px: { xs: 2, md: 4 }, py: 4 }}>
      {/* Keep header as normal but with placeholder count */}
      <Box
        sx={{
          display: "grid",
          gridTemplateColumns: {
            xs: "1fr",
            sm: "repeat(2, 1fr)",
            md: "repeat(3, 1fr)",
          },
          gap: 3.5,
          mt: 2,
        }}
      >
        {Array.from({ length: 6 }).map((_, i) => (
          <Box
            key={i}
            sx={{
              border: "0.5px solid",
              borderColor: "divider",
              borderRadius: 3,
              overflow: "hidden",
            }}
          >
            <Skeleton variant="rectangular" width="100%" sx={{ aspectRatio: "4/3" }} />
            <Box sx={{ p: 2, display: "flex", flexDirection: "column", gap: 1 }}>
              <Skeleton variant="text" width="45%" height={12} />
              <Skeleton variant="text" width="75%" height={18} />
              <Skeleton variant="text" width="100%" height={12} />
              <Skeleton variant="text" width="88%" height={12} />
              <Box sx={{ display: "flex", justifyContent: "space-between", mt: 1 }}>
                <Skeleton variant="rounded" width={60} height={22} />
                <Skeleton variant="rounded" width={80} height={28} />
              </Box>
            </Box>
          </Box>
        ))}
      </Box>
    </Container>
  );
}
```

**Add import:** `import { Skeleton } from "@mui/material";`

